node.text:
I’m so pleased to be part of the #sharethemicfoodandbev campaign, and, indeed, to be sharing the mic with the fabulous @zoeadjonyoh, chef, author and activist and author of Zoe’s Ghana Kitchen. What ‘sharing the mic’ means here is that Zoe will be taking over my Instagram account for 24 hours from 12 midday tomorrow, Monday the 20th, to 12 midday on Tuesday July 21st. You are in for a treat! 
This is a campaign dedicated to amplifying the voices of Black women whose contributions to the food culture have been customarily overlooked, and it’s a real honour to #keepsharingthemic

node.text:
I’ve made a video-selfie with details of how to make my Emergency Brownies for #hopefromhome on #worldhealthday in support of health workers and medical teams. I know that many of you who would like to donate are just not able to right now, but if you can please do, by going to hopefromhome.tiltify.com.
.
#recipeoftheday

user.full_name: P E T R I N A   T I N S L A Y

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Nigella on August 16, 2021 tagging @petrinatinslay. May be an image of food.

node.text:
Should you have any chicken left over from the weekend (doesn’t have to be exactly what’s specified in the recipe, such as it is: it’s more of an idea) #RecipeOfTheDay, a chicken, parsley and almond salad, is a very good place for it! 
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it! 
.
Photograph by @petrinatinslay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Nigella on August 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, food, indoor and text that says 'BBC lifestylÄ Nigella's Cook, Eat, Repeat Premieres 16th August Monday at 7pm (SG/HK)'.

node.text:
I’m thrilled to say that my new series #CookEatRepeat can be seen from tonight on BBC Lifestyle Asia from tonight! And it will be 
available from tomorrow on @bbcplayer . I’m so happy about this. It’s full of the food that brings me great joy, and it is such a pleasure to share it with you. I hope you will be able to join me!
#cookbookcorner

node.text: Meanwhile, over on @foodim, this photograph of a batch of beautiful brioche feuilleté by @beeeze - the product of what she brilliantly calls “pootle-baking” - is #postoftheweek. And if you would like the recipe, hasten over to the @foodim insta page

node.text:
I’m really sorry to be so hideously late with #RecipeOfTheDay. It’s a great favourite: Italian Roast Chicken with Peppers and Olives (and I sometimes add a tumble of unpeeled garlic cloves to the pan, too). And if you don’t eat meat, I must tell you that by using more of all the leeks and peppers etc, and leaving out the chicken (and you could scatter feta over at the end, once it’s cooked) it is a divine vegetable dish
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it!
.
Photograph by @petrinatinslay

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Nigella on August 14, 2021 tagging @foodim, and @rex.goldsmith. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text:
Continuing my feasting from yesterday’s haul from @rex.goldsmith, butterflied sardines (cooked quickly in a very hot oven, with olive oil, garlic, chilli flakes, orange zest, and a spritz of lemon) with a watercress and red chicory salad, with toasted pine nuts and dill. I probably should have grilled the sardines, and I certainly overdressed the salad, but it was just lovely all the same.

It’s not on the floor, by the way, although it does rather look like that: it’s the slightly worn slate-topped table I have in the garden!

node.text:
#RecipeOfTheDay is a lazy delight: No-Churn Margarita Ice Cream! The metric measurements for the booze seem to be missing in the ingredients, though: the 2 tablespoons of tequila = 30ml; the 3 tablespoons Cointreau (or Triple Sec or Grand Marnier) = 45ml. Have fun!
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it!
.
Photograph by Lis Parsons

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Nigella on August 13, 2021 tagging @hgwalter, @foodim, and @rex.goldsmith. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text:
I have had the most fabulous eating day! Earlier, I had *the* best bacon sandwich of my life, made with a couple of thick slices of my old-fashioned sandwich loaf and some Iberico bacon from @hgwalter; bread dunked in the fat, and smeared with English mustard, of course. I kept the rest of the fat, and just now added garlic, parsley and some marjoram, heated it up, threw in some beautiful clams from @rex.goldsmith followed by dry white vermouth, plonked the lid on and left them to steam while I part-cooked a handful or two of orzo; I let it finish cooking in the bacony, garlicky clam liquor. It would have looked more photogenic had I left some of the clams in their shells, but I wanted to be able to shovel it in unimpeded. I’m sure you understand…

(And I’ve kept the water the orzo the pasta was par-cooked in for my next loaf of bread)

What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. A meatloaf may not be a beauty but, made right, can be a joy. #RecipeOfTheDay is my Mini Meatloaves which are, indeed, not pretty but very glad-making!
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it!
.
Photograph by Lis Parsons
